The purpose of the District shall be:
(a) to perpetuate the old American institution, the barbershop quartet, and to promote and encourage
vocal harmony and good fellowship among its members throughout the Evergreen District by the
formation in every city, town and hamlet, of local chapters, composed of members interested in the
purposes of this corporation, which shall be the same as the purposes of the Society;
(b) to hold annual, local and district contests in quartet and chorus singing;
(c) to encourage and promote the education of its members and the public in music appreciation;
(d) to initiate, promote and participate in charitable projects; and
(e) to promote public appreciation of barbershop quartet and chorus singing by publication and
dissemination thereof.
